                            <comment id="13696214" author="ivanmi" created="Sat, 29 Jun 2013 23:25:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The issue is in the test, it&apos;s a race condition between threads starting up:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; Server server = RPC.getServer(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; TestImpl(), ADDRESS,
        0, 5, &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;, conf);
    server.start();   &amp;lt;--- starts the reader threads asynchronously
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;and test asserting that at least one thread started:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;      &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; threadsRunning = countThreads(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Server$Listener$Reader&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);
      assertTrue(threadsRunning &amp;gt; 0);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Will attach the patch shortly. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
